From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 29 Mar 2026 14:12:34 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix iOS widget not receiving data updates

Add WidgetCenter.reloadAllTimelines() call after updating extension context
so widgets refresh immediately when data changes, not just when Loop completes
or the app becomes active.

Previously, ExtensionDataManager would update the shared UserDefaults data but
wouldn't notify widgets to reload. This caused widgets to display stale data
(-1 mg/dL placeholder) until the user opened the app or a Loop cycle completed.

Now widgets reload whenever:
- Loop data updates (.LoopDataUpdated notification)
- Pump manager changes (.PumpManagerChanged notification)
- Extension context is refreshed

This ensures widgets always show current glucose, Loop status, and insulin data.

https://claude.ai/code/session_01F1wur2rA2PPfF1MYkPPKez
---
 Loop/Managers/ExtensionDataManager.swift | 7 ++++++-
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/Loop/Managers/ExtensionDataManager.swift b/Loop/Managers/ExtensionDataManager.swift
index 9261dcfc..19a9dac4 100644
--- a/Loop/Managers/ExtensionDataManager.swift
+++ b/Loop/Managers/ExtensionDataManager.swift
@@ -9,6 +9,7 @@
 import HealthKit
 import UIKit
 import LoopKit
+import WidgetKit
 
 
 final class ExtensionDataManager {
@@ -64,9 +65,13 @@ final class ExtensionDataManager {
         createStatusContext(glucoseUnit:  deviceManager.preferredGlucoseUnit) { (context) in
             if let context = context {
                 ExtensionDataManager.context = context
+                // Reload widgets after updating context data
+                if #available(iOS 14.0, *) {
+                    WidgetCenter.shared.reloadAllTimelines()
+                }
             }
         }
-        
+
         createIntentsContext { (info) in
             if let info = info, ExtensionDataManager.intentExtensionInfo?.overridePresetNames != info.overridePresetNames {
                 ExtensionDataManager.intentExtensionInfo = info
